TY  - JOUR
AU  - Agrawal, Ashwini
AU  - Hacamo, Isaac
AU  - Hu, Zhongchen
T1  - Information Dispersion across Employees and Stock Returns
PY  - 2021
Y1  - 2021/10/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhaa105
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 34
IS  - 10
SP  - 4785
EP  - 4831
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - Rank-and-file employees are becoming increasingly critical for many firms, yet we know little about how their employment dynamics matter for stock prices. We analyze new data from the individual CV’s of public company employees and find that rank-and-file labor flows can be used to predict abnormal stock returns. Accounting data and survey evidence indicate that workers’ labor market decisions reflect information about future corporate earnings. Investors, however, do not appear to fully incorporate this information into their earnings expectations. The findings support the hypothesis that rank-and-file employees’ entry and exit decisions reveal valuable insights into their employers’ future stock performance.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhaa105
ER  - 



