TY  - JOUR
AU  - Frank, Murray Z
AU  - Sanati, Ali
T1  - Financing Corporate Growth
PY  - 2021
Y1  - 2021/10/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhaa133
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 34
IS  - 10
SP  - 4926
EP  - 4998
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - Considerable research tackles the aggregate impact of debt financing. We show that equity is more important for firm growth than generally understood. A dollar of equity issuance is associated with an extra $\$0.93$ of real assets, whereas a dollar of debt issuance is associated with an extra $\$0.14$. Firms issue equity first, then increase real assets, and, finally, issue debt while repurchasing equity. We explain this sequence using a model in which debt is tax preferred relative to equity but is subject to limited commitment. We use the estimated model to evaluate how several government policies affect corporate growth.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhaa133
ER  - 



