TY  - JOUR
AU  - Ahmad, Muhammad Farooq
AU  - de Bodt, Eric
AU  - Harford, Jarrad
T1  - International Trade and the Propagation of Merger Waves
PY  - 2021
Y1  - 2021/10/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhaa104
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 34
IS  - 10
SP  - 4876
EP  - 4925
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - Cross-border merger activity is growing in importance. We map the global trade network each year from 1989 to 2016 and compare it to cross-border and domestic merger activity. Trade-weighted merger activity in trading partner countries has statistically and economically significant explanatory power for the likelihood that a given country will be in a merger wave state, at both the cross-border and domestic levels, even controlling for its own lagged merger activity. The role of trade as a channel for transmitting merger waves is confirmed using import tariff cuts and trade sanctions as instruments to mitigate endogeneity. Overall, the full trade network helps our understanding of merger waves and how merger activity propagate across borders.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhaa104
ER  - 



